For firmware analysis and security research, it is essential to understand both the capabilities and the risks of diagnostic features. Implementing custom, persistent diagnostic modules with covert telemetry channels can introduce significant security vulnerabilities, including unauthorized data exfiltration and system compromise. Instead, rely on standard, well-tested debugging and diagnostic tools that provide secure and reliable access to system information. Always follow secure coding practices and ensure that diagnostic features are properly secured and disabled in production environments.

